snippet.textDisplay:
As a fellow Katamari fan, I'll have to warn you that the Vita version has very little content, almost an embarassing amount. I cruised through it in a mere 3 hours. So if you ever get it, don't expect too much.

The soundtrack is awesome though.

snippet.textDisplay: Why do I like this song? Why is there a mandrill eating on the soundtrack's cover? I usually add tracks I like to this list without thinking too much but I'll admit it took me a couple minutes to convince myself to upload this one. At the same time, a song and a cover like this isn't that surprising when it comes to the Katamari Damacy series. If I ever get a Vita, I'll buy this game so I can get a good dose of happiness.
